def: The act of collecting or gathering together scattered cattle byriding around them and driving them in. [Western U.S.]
A stud, or collection of breeding horses and mares; also, aplace for keeping a stud. [Obs.]King Henry the Eighth erected a noble studdery. Holinshed.
Toward, or in the direction of, the east.
Situated above the foot of a mollusk; as, the suprapedal gland.
An order of vitreous sponges, having glassy six-rayed,siliceous spicules; -- called also Hexactinellinæ.
A photographic picture copied from the negative on glass; aphotographic transparency. R. Hunt.
In a bibulous manner; with profuse imbibition or absorption. DeQuincey.
According to number; in number; numerically.
Any species of small moths of the genus Procris. The larvæ ofsome species injure the grapevine by feeding in groups upon theleaves.
